WEBVTT

00:11.928 --> 00:13.888
<i>Why do people do
the things they do?</i>

00:15.557 --> 00:17.934
<i>I never thought it was that complicated.</i>

00:20.603 --> 00:22.313
<i>You do what seems right</i>

00:22.313 --> 00:23.314
<i>in the moment.</i>

00:25.650 --> 00:27.318
<i>When I first met Topper,</i>

00:27.944 --> 00:30.530
<i>I just thought he was the perfect guy.</i>

00:31.781 --> 00:32.782
<i>Polite,</i>

00:33.575 --> 00:34.576
<i>sweet,</i>

00:35.660 --> 00:37.370
<i>from a good family.</i>

00:38.788 --> 00:40.749
<i>He was everything John B wasn't.</i>

00:42.751 --> 00:47.547
<i>- But the heart wants what it wants.</i>

00:48.173 --> 00:51.259
<i>And now,
after everything that's happened,</i>

00:52.844 --> 00:54.387
<i>it doesn't seem so simple.</i>

01:04.147 --> 01:07.108
- All right, I'm starving.
- Yeah, same.

01:07.108 --> 01:09.611
Time to smother your hunger.

01:09.611 --> 01:12.322
- Who says that?
- I'm never gonna say that again.

01:12.322 --> 01:14.157
I'm sorry.

01:15.575 --> 01:18.495
I had a really good time yesterday.

01:20.455 --> 01:24.209
It was nice to have a day, a single day,

01:25.293 --> 01:27.504
without it being about...

01:28.046 --> 01:31.883
- About trying to run from the cops and...
- Yeah.

01:31.883 --> 01:33.468
Jacking your dad's truck.

01:33.468 --> 01:36.888
Oh yeah. Thanks for that.
He was super happy. It was perfect.

01:40.266 --> 01:41.768
You know what? Thank you.

01:45.105 --> 01:46.815
I was in a really rough spot.

01:50.360 --> 01:52.195
I had a really great time with you.

01:52.779 --> 01:56.825
And, uh, yeah, Sarah,
I've been thinking about you a lot.

01:56.825 --> 01:59.244
I'm sure you already know that.

01:59.994 --> 02:02.038
I just can't imagine everything

02:02.038 --> 02:04.040
you got going on with your dad,

02:04.040 --> 02:07.252
your family,
and then the other people in your life.

02:07.836 --> 02:08.711
Hey, Sally.

02:08.711 --> 02:11.589
So I understand
if you just wanna take a second

02:12.090 --> 02:13.258
to breathe.

02:13.925 --> 02:14.843
Shit.

02:16.094 --> 02:17.220
You okay?

02:18.012 --> 02:19.722
- What?
- It's... it's Kiara.

02:19.722 --> 02:21.516
Ki... Oh.

02:21.516 --> 02:23.726
Is that okay?

02:27.689 --> 02:29.816
- And she saw us.
- Yeah.

02:32.235 --> 02:35.196
Here you go. Have a good day.

02:39.576 --> 02:40.535
Kie!

02:42.370 --> 02:43.705
Kie, wait, can we...

02:43.705 --> 02:47.250
- Topper and I were getting breakfast.
-  It's none of my business.

02:47.250 --> 02:49.669
That's it. You should join if you want to.

02:50.879 --> 02:51.796
Breakfast?

02:52.422 --> 02:54.048
Yeah, breakfast.

02:54.632 --> 02:56.217
Yo, Kie!

02:56.801 --> 02:58.052
Yo, Top.

02:59.929 --> 03:01.681
I had nowhere to go last night.

03:01.681 --> 03:05.894
Cleo's at Pope's. I couldn't find JJ.
John B and I got into, like, a thing.

03:05.894 --> 03:08.813
I'm-- He found me and took me to Mase
with a group of people.

03:08.813 --> 03:12.317
Okay, so you bring him to the Middle
of the Island Restaurant on a Saturday?

03:12.317 --> 03:14.319
Kie! What's up? Random, right?

03:15.403 --> 03:16.487
Look, I'm just gonna go.

03:16.487 --> 03:18.656
- So I don't want to impose.
- Oh, perfect.

03:19.199 --> 03:21.367
Gotta help my parents
set up for their party.

03:21.367 --> 03:23.369
You know what? I'm gonna go too.

03:23.369 --> 03:26.206
Wait. Wait, what?
Our food literally just came out.

03:26.206 --> 03:29.417
- I know.
- How are you gonna smother your hunger?

03:30.752 --> 03:32.462
- Topper. Um...
- Yeah, I'm leaving.

03:32.462 --> 03:33.838
I'm going with Kie.

03:33.838 --> 03:34.923
But thank you.

03:37.300 --> 03:38.468
I'm gonna call you.

03:43.681 --> 03:44.807
All right.

03:45.934 --> 03:46.935
See you, Sarah.

03:49.896 --> 03:51.439
Sarah, what are you doing?

03:54.359 --> 03:55.360
I don't know.

03:56.361 --> 03:59.322
-  Walk me through it one more time.
- Okay, right there.

03:59.322 --> 04:02.075
That's where they're taking him.
That's the site of the idol.

04:02.575 --> 04:05.745
You pointed to just South America,
you understand that, right?

04:06.412 --> 04:07.288
Yep.

04:08.790 --> 04:11.084
That's all you know?
He's somewhere in South America?

04:11.084 --> 04:13.711
That's why we're going
to the professor's house.

04:13.711 --> 04:15.421
- Look, he was at the site.
- Okay.

04:15.421 --> 04:17.590
So happy we have the map, then.

04:17.590 --> 04:20.593
Wait. Whoa, whoa! We're going
to a house now with a dead body in it?

04:20.593 --> 04:23.179
- That... that's where we're going?
- Yeah.

04:23.179 --> 04:25.932
And if the cops show up,
you know what that makes us look like?

04:27.141 --> 04:27.976
Yes.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.937
Okay, just making sure.

04:31.813 --> 04:34.315
Can we make it quick though?
Just in and out.

04:51.833 --> 04:53.293
His body's gone.

04:54.085 --> 04:55.503
Sowell was right here.

04:56.004 --> 04:58.464
- And Sowell was the...
- The professor.

04:58.965 --> 05:02.010
Right. No, I know what happened.
They've already been here, John B.

05:02.010 --> 05:05.263
They sent in the sweepers and now probably
decontaminated this entire room.

05:05.263 --> 05:08.057
- There's nothing left. We should get out.
- Maybe there's something.

05:08.057 --> 05:09.851
Okay, what are we looking for then?

05:09.851 --> 05:12.228
Anything to do with an archaeological dig.

05:12.228 --> 05:15.356
- Oh, thanks. That really narrows it down.
-  I'm trying.

05:15.857 --> 05:19.235
- Anything. All righty. Fricking anything.

05:19.819 --> 05:20.903
Seriously, man?

05:22.280 --> 05:24.866
Wait! Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Don't leave your fingerprints, bro.

05:24.866 --> 05:26.826
This is a live crime scene, dude.

05:28.494 --> 05:31.247
Yeah, you know, actually,
I'm just gonna look in the kitchen.

05:31.247 --> 05:34.083
- No one ever checks the fridge.
- Yeah, go for that, man.

05:39.630 --> 05:40.757
We were right here.

05:45.261 --> 05:47.388
Dad, Sowell, the idol.

05:47.889 --> 05:49.307
<i>Tommy. Hey.</i>

05:52.060 --> 05:54.687
The temalacatl,
it asks a question.

05:55.563 --> 05:56.814
<i>The idol.</i>

05:56.814 --> 05:58.399
- The gnomon--

06:00.151 --> 06:02.362
Gnomon what, Tommy?
Gnomon what?

06:02.362 --> 06:03.863
<i>Kalinago.</i>

06:04.697 --> 06:05.698
<i>Temalacatl.</i>

06:18.252 --> 06:19.295
JJ.

06:20.838 --> 06:21.672
- JJ!
- Hmm?

06:22.799 --> 06:25.009
What is it? Snack time? What are we doing?

06:25.009 --> 06:27.470
You know what?
I feel very judged right now.

06:27.470 --> 06:28.596
- Sure.
- All right?

06:28.596 --> 06:31.182
There's an entire bird in here
that'll just go to waste, okay?

06:31.182 --> 06:33.893
I'm not gonna let that happen.
It's not like I'm stealing it.

06:33.893 --> 06:36.479
No one else is gonna eat it.
I was like, "I'll take the nutrients

06:36.479 --> 06:39.649
that this beautiful bird gives me
and fill the tank," all right?

06:39.649 --> 06:41.734
- I haven't been able to eat anything--
- JJ. Hey.

06:42.443 --> 06:43.694
- Find something?
- Yeah.

06:45.822 --> 06:47.949
"Local expedition team
departs for South America."

06:48.616 --> 06:49.909
One of these guys is Sowell?

06:50.535 --> 06:51.411
Right there.

06:51.911 --> 06:52.954
All right.

06:53.913 --> 06:55.498
-  Holy shit.
-  What?

06:55.498 --> 06:56.457
Neville.

06:57.291 --> 06:58.209
- What?
- Neville.

06:58.209 --> 07:00.753
The last things Sowell said
before he died was "Neville."

07:00.753 --> 07:02.713
- Neville, meaning...
-  Right there.

07:02.713 --> 07:04.549
Neville Persaud,

07:04.549 --> 07:06.134
expedition guide.

07:08.261 --> 07:10.430
So Sowell said,
"Five people on the expedition," right?

07:10.430 --> 07:11.889
- Right.
- Three of those people died.

07:11.889 --> 07:13.141
Which leaves us with two.

07:13.724 --> 07:15.184
- Sowell.
- Mm-hmm.

07:15.184 --> 07:16.352
Neville.

07:16.352 --> 07:18.271
- Yeah.
- He's the last one alive.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.898
Yeah, I think
Sowell was telling me to warn him.

07:21.607 --> 07:22.733
We need to find Neville.

07:46.257 --> 07:47.133
Hey, bud.

07:51.095 --> 07:52.013
Dad.

07:52.013 --> 07:53.473
Mm-hmm.

07:54.682 --> 07:57.143
- What the hell are you doing here?

07:57.143 --> 08:01.230
I could see you were in over your head,
so I came back to help you.

08:01.898 --> 08:04.275
-  You wanna help?
-  Yeah.

08:04.275 --> 08:05.359
Leave.

08:05.359 --> 08:09.030
- You can't be here.
- I know you stole the cross, Rafe.

08:12.074 --> 08:14.035
Now, come on. Rafe.

08:16.871 --> 08:18.789
You were tired of living in my shadow.

08:19.832 --> 08:23.085
And you felt like I overstepped.

08:23.085 --> 08:25.963
By giving away something of mine.
Why would I think that?

08:25.963 --> 08:29.634
You were right. I should've talked to you
before I donated it. You deserve that.

08:29.634 --> 08:31.052
Yeah. You should have.

08:31.844 --> 08:32.845
You're right.

08:32.845 --> 08:35.723
That was my mistake, but here we are,
and you have it,

08:35.723 --> 08:37.934
and we gotta be smart with it, okay?

08:37.934 --> 08:40.811
- Yeah.
- This cross is special<i>.</i>

08:40.811 --> 08:42.522
- Okay?
- Listen, the deal is done.

08:44.690 --> 08:45.525
What deal?

08:45.525 --> 08:47.527
- It's done.
- You had no time to get a deal done.

08:47.527 --> 08:50.821
Well, it is done
because I'm selling some of it today.

08:51.948 --> 08:54.951
- What do you mean, some of it?
- I melted that shit down.

08:58.829 --> 09:01.958
- You're joking. You didn't melt it down.
- No, no, I'm not joking.

09:01.958 --> 09:04.835
- Shit. I mean, I can... I'll show you now.
-  Rafe, no.

09:05.628 --> 09:08.589
- I mean, listen, this is just a...
- No, no.

09:09.632 --> 09:12.009
...just a very tiny fraction of it, so...

09:14.554 --> 09:16.138
You melted it?

09:16.138 --> 09:19.225
Yeah, I melted the Cross of Santo Domingo.
Yep, melted it.

09:19.225 --> 09:22.186
- How could you do that, Rafe?
-  I'm trying to make money off this.

09:22.186 --> 09:23.229
What? Why?

09:23.229 --> 09:26.357
Because you can't trace spare parts, Dad.
What are you talking about?

09:26.357 --> 09:29.819
Spare parts? It's...
It's priceless! It's one of a kind!

09:29.819 --> 09:31.362
-  What is the issue?
- Oh my God.

09:31.362 --> 09:34.407
I don't understand.
Tell me. Can you enlighten me?

09:34.407 --> 09:38.244
Look, even if you don't care about it
at all, it's lost all its value.

09:38.244 --> 09:39.245
- It's a relic.
- Whatever.

09:39.245 --> 09:42.331
- You can't melt down the cross!
- Yes, I can. Just stop, stop!

09:43.541 --> 09:45.084
I'm talking now!

09:46.252 --> 09:48.421
All right? This isn't about you!

09:53.134 --> 09:55.928
I mean, I was...
I was held hostage at Singh's,

09:56.512 --> 09:58.764
locked up, not knowing
if I was gonna live or die,

09:58.764 --> 10:01.475
and I thought, "If I get out,
I'm not going to sit around

10:01.475 --> 10:03.519
and wait for a handout from you."

10:04.854 --> 10:07.773
- I was gonna take what's mine, okay?

10:08.274 --> 10:09.317
Rightfully mine.

10:11.068 --> 10:12.153
Do you understand?

10:12.737 --> 10:13.988
- Yes.
- You get it?

10:13.988 --> 10:15.072
- Yeah.
- Good.

10:19.702 --> 10:21.037
Okay. Okay, Rafe.

10:21.537 --> 10:23.873
- What's done is done.
- Yeah, it is done.

10:23.873 --> 10:25.875
Now we gotta move forward, okay?

10:25.875 --> 10:28.210
You gotta do the things
I sent you here to do, all right?

10:28.210 --> 10:30.921
So we can go back to Guadeloupe,
and we'll start again.

10:30.921 --> 10:32.715
- Listen.
- We'll get a brand-new life.

10:32.715 --> 10:34.634
- I wanna start again too.
- Okay, good.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.969
- Okay, but not in Guadeloupe.
- What?

10:36.969 --> 10:39.305
Why the hell would I start over there?

10:40.723 --> 10:43.893
Because we can't stay here, son.

10:43.893 --> 10:44.935
No.

10:45.603 --> 10:48.731
No, <i>you</i> can't stay here. I can.

10:50.858 --> 10:53.694
I mean, I got a crew here.
I... I got... I got my home.

10:54.570 --> 10:59.283
Okay, Dad, what I'm saying is,
I don't need you anymore.

11:02.620 --> 11:03.537
I'm good.

11:05.998 --> 11:07.875
Rafe, Rafe, Rafe, Rafe, listen to me.

11:11.170 --> 11:13.714
What are you gonna do? You gonna hit me?

11:13.714 --> 11:15.466
- Rafe.
- With your cane?

11:17.385 --> 11:19.804
I'm gonna sell my gold.

11:19.804 --> 11:21.097
Okay? My gold.

11:22.056 --> 11:23.474
I'm gonna do whatever else I want,

11:23.474 --> 11:26.268
and there's actually nothing
you can do about it, okay?

11:33.192 --> 11:34.318
Go home, Dad.

11:41.701 --> 11:44.537
All right, Sarah.
It's time to come clean.

11:44.537 --> 11:45.955
What happened?

11:45.955 --> 11:47.123
You and Topper?

11:47.123 --> 11:48.082
Oh God!

11:49.667 --> 11:51.502
It's actually so embarrassing.

11:53.337 --> 11:57.091
He caught me
slugging beer at the Tiki Bar.

11:57.091 --> 11:58.801
- You weren't.
- Yeah.

11:58.801 --> 12:00.219
Shot drinking.

12:00.928 --> 12:03.639
- I'm not judging.
- I wouldn't blame you if you were.

12:05.766 --> 12:10.187
And then a couple kids from KCD rolled up,
and they were already going to Mase.

12:10.813 --> 12:12.064
And then...

12:13.899 --> 12:14.734
I kissed him.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.610
<i>♪ Look in the mirror ♪</i>

12:17.653 --> 12:18.904
<i>♪ Who do you see? ♪</i>

12:19.488 --> 12:20.573
Do you hate me?

12:23.534 --> 12:24.869
Hate's the wrong word.

12:27.037 --> 12:28.122
<i>♪ Someone familiar... ♪</i>

12:28.122 --> 12:30.040
So you and John B are just done?

12:30.040 --> 12:33.669
No. Well, I don't know.
I don't want to be.

12:33.669 --> 12:37.465
Like since the island,
everything has felt so... abnormal,

12:37.465 --> 12:40.176
and it just felt nice
to feel something normal again.

12:40.176 --> 12:41.510
And I, like...

12:44.138 --> 12:45.097
I'm a mess.

12:46.515 --> 12:47.933
I feel like such a mess.

12:50.853 --> 12:53.063
I think we're all a little messed up.

12:54.273 --> 12:55.232
Yeah.

12:56.150 --> 12:57.151
You,

12:57.151 --> 12:58.194
me,

12:58.694 --> 12:59.653
JJ.

13:01.530 --> 13:05.117
He stole that money clip from my dad,
and I'm still pissed about it.

13:05.701 --> 13:08.746
Just pretending he doesn't care.
He won't talk to me.

13:11.373 --> 13:13.334
- I'd rather argue about it.
- Right.

13:17.630 --> 13:18.839
Wheezie?

13:18.839 --> 13:19.882
What?

13:19.882 --> 13:21.592
I texted her when we got in.

13:21.592 --> 13:24.970
<i>Sarah,
don't be mad, but I ran away.</i>

13:24.970 --> 13:27.389
<i>I'm in the OBX, and I have to see you.</i>

13:28.015 --> 13:30.518
<i>Come to our rental condo
on Greensboro Street, okay?</i>

13:31.018 --> 13:33.145
<i>But, Sarah, please don't tell anyone.</i>

13:46.742 --> 13:50.538
Okay, now, so let me get this straight.
So, because you know a guy

13:50.538 --> 13:53.457
with the same last name as Neville,
you think they've gotta be related.

13:53.457 --> 13:55.668
- That's your master plan?
- Right. Okay.

13:55.668 --> 13:58.462
How many people do you know
with the last name Persaud?

13:58.462 --> 14:00.589
I met a guy here
last summer with my cousin

14:00.589 --> 14:03.634
'cause we're doing
the growing business. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

14:03.634 --> 14:05.344
Last name Persaud.

14:05.344 --> 14:07.137
Or wait, was it Percett?

14:07.137 --> 14:09.181
- No, no, no. Okay, you think--
- No, no, no.

14:09.181 --> 14:13.269
- 'Cause we're talking about my dad's life.
- No, I know. I know Mr. Persaud.

14:13.269 --> 14:14.770
Trust me. It's cool.

14:14.770 --> 14:16.689
Hey, uh, Mr. P, right?

14:16.689 --> 14:18.232
- Hey!
-  Yeah. I told you.

14:18.232 --> 14:20.150
Yeah, yeah, yeah. What's going on, man?

14:20.150 --> 14:23.737
Yeah. Hey, so we're looking for...
we're looking for Neville.

14:23.737 --> 14:26.740
- Is he still here?
- Nah, nah, nah, he's out there.

14:26.740 --> 14:29.785
- Been holding up near Doe Creek.
- Doe Creek?

14:29.785 --> 14:31.996
In his houseboat. Way, way back.

14:33.706 --> 14:34.748
Why you ever doubt me?

14:34.748 --> 14:37.418
The idea was a little far-fetched
is all I'm saying.

14:38.210 --> 14:39.795
All right, so we're looking for

14:40.379 --> 14:41.630
a houseboat.

14:44.091 --> 14:47.219
-  That looks like a houseboat.
- Well, you think he's there?

14:47.219 --> 14:49.513
- I don't know. I mean--
- Only one way to find out.

14:49.513 --> 14:50.764
Neville! Hey!

14:50.764 --> 14:52.308
- Stop it!
- Dude, what?

14:52.308 --> 14:55.269
What are you talking about, what?
He thinks people are trying to kill him.

14:55.269 --> 14:56.687
He's probably packing.

14:57.396 --> 14:59.064
Ah, okay. It's a death trap.

14:59.565 --> 15:01.400
Yeah, unfortunately,
we don't have a choice.

15:01.984 --> 15:04.278
He's the only guy alive
who knows where my dad is.

15:19.501 --> 15:21.128
JJ, keep it down.

15:31.972 --> 15:34.516
The stove's warm.
He's still here.

15:41.148 --> 15:43.692
- Maybe he split when he heard us coming.
- Devils!

15:46.111 --> 15:48.989
Sir! Listen! Neville! We just wanna talk.

15:48.989 --> 15:50.991
John B! Trip line! Trip line!

15:54.203 --> 15:57.206
- No, no, no, no!
- Let him go!

15:57.206 --> 16:00.250
- Stop, stop! We know Professor Sowell.
- Who gave you that name?

16:00.250 --> 16:01.293
Let it go, dude!

16:01.293 --> 16:03.212
- Listen to me, we're friends, okay?
- Hey!

16:03.212 --> 16:07.341
You were in Orinoco last year!
With five other people. Right?

16:08.008 --> 16:10.427
- How did you know that?
- Let go, let go.

16:10.427 --> 16:11.762
Let it go!

16:11.762 --> 16:13.681
- Let it go!

16:16.100 --> 16:18.477
We're on the same team, home dog, okay?

16:18.477 --> 16:20.688
Look, we don't wanna hurt you, okay?

16:22.773 --> 16:23.857
Put it down.

16:25.484 --> 16:26.402
Jesus.

16:26.402 --> 16:28.570
Look, we were just with Sowell yesterday.

16:29.613 --> 16:30.572
He, uh...

16:32.241 --> 16:33.367
He didn't make it.

16:34.994 --> 16:35.911
He's dead?

16:37.121 --> 16:38.122
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

16:39.623 --> 16:40.457
I'm sorry.

16:43.168 --> 16:44.169
You good?

16:47.089 --> 16:48.424
I'm the last one left.

16:50.759 --> 16:51.927
Yeah.

16:54.096 --> 16:56.473
That's why we had to get to you
before they did.

16:58.851 --> 16:59.935
If we found you,

17:00.769 --> 17:01.687
they can too.

17:03.188 --> 17:04.857
I just have a few questions.

17:06.942 --> 17:09.236
Solana, you've been there. Yeah?

17:10.487 --> 17:11.989
That is a place of evil.

17:13.407 --> 17:14.241
Okay.

17:14.241 --> 17:16.035
That stone piece right there.

17:17.494 --> 17:20.205
Me and my dad found the thingy
that goes in the center.

17:20.205 --> 17:21.915
- The gnomon.
-  Gnomon.

17:21.915 --> 17:25.002
- What's a gnomon?
- The gnomon. Hey, I got it. I got it.

17:25.002 --> 17:25.961
Listen to me.

17:25.961 --> 17:29.548
